data.meta_description: Princess Margaret of Denmark (1895-1992) . She was a daughter of Prince Valdemar of Denmark, youngest son of Christian IX of Denm & Princess Marie d'Orleans. She was the first Danish princess since the Reformation born a Roman Catholic. She married a Catholic prince, her mother's relative, Prince René of Bourbon-Parma Prince René of Bourbon-Parma  (1894 –1962). the couple had three son and a daughter. they live for many years in France but after World War II settled back in Denmark.
